Project Idea: Task Manager

Basic Story:
Develop a Task Manager application that helps users organize and manage their tasks effectively. Users can add, edit, delete, and mark tasks as completed. The application will provide a clean and intuitive interface for managing tasks.

Core Features of MVP:

Task Input: Allow users to input new tasks with a title and optional description.
Task Display: Display the list of tasks with options to view details, edit, delete, and mark as completed.
Task Status: Provide visual indicators for the status of each task (e.g., completed, pending).
CRUD Operations: Implement functionalities to add, edit, delete, and mark tasks as completed.
Data Persistence: Persist task data locally so that tasks remain saved even after page reloads.
Challenges Expected:

Data Management: Implementing CRUD operations for tasks and managing task data effectively.
User Interface: Designing an intuitive and user-friendly interface for managing tasks.
Data Persistence: Implementing local storage or other methods for persisting task data.
Meeting Project Requirements:

HTML/CSS/JS Frontend: Utilize HTML for structure, CSS for styling, and JavaScript for interactivity.
Data Management: Implement CRUD operations for managing tasks.
User Interface: Design a clean and intuitive interface for users to interact with tasks.
Data Persistence: Ensure task data is persisted locally using methods like local storage.
Stretch Goals:

User Authentication: Implement user accounts to allow multiple users to manage their tasks.
Filtering and Sorting: Add options to filter and sort tasks based on different criteria (e.g., due date, priority).
Reminders and Notifications: Integrate reminders and notifications for upcoming tasks or deadlines.
Task Categories: Allow users to categorize tasks into different categories or projects.
This project idea provides a practical application for managing tasks effectively and offers opportunities for implementing various features and enhancements to improve task management capabilities. It also allows for creativity in designing the user interface and user experience.
